'''Docufilm''' [dok-yuh-film] noun, adjective

- ''noun''
1. A film or video production, presenting personal, social, political or historical subject matter in a factually accurate and informative or entertaining manner that often consists of archival footage and/or interviews supported by narration.

- ''adjective''
1. Broadcast or theatrical production. which presents factually accurate elements based on or re-creating an actual event or series of events, personal experiences, etc.: ''a docufilm plight of American veterans.''